Package: iklSurvML
Type: Package
Title: Optimized Survival Machine Learning with Fixed 117 Algorithm Combinations
Version: 1.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("sher-l", email = "sher-l@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("cre", "aut"))
  )
Author: sher-l [cre, aut]
Maintainer: sher-l <sher-l@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: An optimized R package for survival analysis using machine learning.
    Provides a fixed Mime-style 117-combination all-mode grid across 10 ML algorithms (RSF,
    Enet, StepCox, CoxBoost, plsRcox, SuperPC, GBM, survival-SVM, Ridge, Lasso)
    with feature selection caching for improved performance. Includes tools for
    developing prognostic models, feature selection, and performance visualization.
